<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="concept_opg_tyg_4z">
 <title>Define the CRUD Operation</title>
 <conbody>
        <p><indexterm>Salesforce destination<indexterm>CRUD operation</indexterm></indexterm>The
            Salesforce destination can insert, update, upsert, delete, or undelete data. To upsert
            data, you must specify the external ID column to use. </p>
        <p>The destination writes the records based on the CRUD operation defined in a CRUD
            operation header attribute or in operation-related stage properties:<dl>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt>CRUD record header attribute</dt>
                    <dd
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/RecordHeaderAtt"/>
                    <dd>The attribute can contain one of the following numeric values:<ul
                            id="ul_smy_qf3_1y">
                            <li>1 for INSERT</li>
                            <li>2 for DELETE</li>
                            <li>3 for UPDATE</li>
                            <li>4 for UPSERT</li>
                            <li>5 for unsupported operations</li>
                            <li>6 for UNDELETED</li>
                        </ul></dd>
                    <dd
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DefineRecordHeaderAtt"
                    />
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt>Operation stage properties</dt>
                    <dd
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DefaultOperation"/>
                    <dd
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/UnsupportedOp"
                    />
                </dlentry>
            </dl></p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
